subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.

Astyanax pirapuan

represents the first report of 

A. scabripinnis

species complex in the Rio 
Paraguay
basin. Recent description have demonstrated that species of this complex have restricted geographical distributions (

e.g. 
Astyanax brachypterygium
; 
A. cremnobates
; 
A. ita
; 
A. ojiara
; 
A. paris
; 
A. totae
; 
A. troya
; 
A. turmalinensis

; 

A. goyanensis

; 

A. courensis

), which also seems to occur with 

A. pirapuan

, as we have been collecting in many river basins and it has not been reported in other regions.
